		<td><b>Toxicity of ROM chips...</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here's a rather unusual question that occupies my mind lately... what negative health effects might there be from consuming alcohol mixed with ROM chips in it?
<br />
<br />The background is I've lately been dressing up as a pirate at masquerades. And as we all know, a pirate's favorite drink consists of rum... which is actually spelt "rom" in Swedish. I guess you can all see the extremely geeky pun by now <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />And while having a "bottle o' ROM" filled with NES ROM chips and some worn-out EPROMs is geeky enough, it's not very drinkable and leaves me with having to keep a bottle of actual rum as well. 
<br />
<br />So I am considering going against all "never mix, never worry" warnings and mixing my drinkable rum with the ROM/EPROM chips in one unified bottle... but am worried that the health effects might be worse than a damaged liver.
<br />
<br />Anyone got any thoughts on this?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


